Judul: Exoplanet hunter will seek worlds close to home: NASA���s mission is designed to spot planets orbiting nearby bright stars.
Abstrak:
Filling the shoes of NASA’s Kepler spacecraft won’t be easy. Since its launch in 2009, Kepler has discovered nearly threequarters of the 3,700-plus known exoplanets. And there are thousands more candidates
waiting to be confirmed.
